w23b42pdn2.name: Ahmad Ibrahim Mosque
w23b42pdn2.remarks: Built in 1958, this old generation zinc-roofed mosque located in the North part of the island serves the religious needs of Muslim living and working in the vicinity. It can accommodate 200 Muslims at any one time. It offers nursery, kindergarten and weekend madrasah classes for children of nearby residents. Altogether, a total of 480 children attend classes at various times, at the masjid. Since the â€˜70s, there have been several renovation and repair works carried out.

w23b4u6c2h.directions: Head to the lift lobby on level 4, nect to Kid@Play waterpark. The lift lobby is right beside the washroom. Enter the staircase landing in front of the cargo lifts. Musolla is on the top floor.
w23b4u6c2h.name: Northpoint
w23b4u6c2h.remarks: Not an official praying area. Shared male & female area. Provision found in the hosereel cabinet.

w23b4v996h.name: Darul Makmur Mosque
w23b4v996h.remarks: Morning is a hectic period at the masjid when doting parents wave their pre-schoolers goodbye. Besides kindergarten classes for these pre-schoolers, the mosque is among the few, which offers a Tahfiz (Al-Quran memorization) course for children. Built in 1989, it serves Muslim families living in Yishun and the North part of the island. The masjid, which falls under Phase Two of the Mosque Building Fund, can accommodate about 3000 people.

w23b4u5qwp.name: Northpoint City, Lift Lobby B
w23b4u5qwp.directions:
1) Face Poh Kim DVD library at Basement 2, turn left and walk towards the carpark. Enter carpark and head towards C6 parking lot. Musollah will be visible from there.

2) At Basement 1 near Beauty Language and Spectacle Hut, head towards lift lobby B and take travellator down. The musollah will be located beneath the travellator.
